# govulncheck suppression file (spec §15 step 3, line 3459)
#
# From v0.2.0, govulncheck is a BLOCKING release gate in .github/workflows/release.yml.
# Each line below suppresses one finding. Lines starting with "#" are comments.
#
# Format (one per line):
#   GO-NNNN-NNNNN  # rationale: <one-line justification>; reviewed-by: <name>; expires: YYYY-MM-DD
#
# Suppression policy:
#   1. The vulnerability MUST be in a transitive dep with no available patched version, OR
#      the reachable function MUST be proven unreachable at our use site (link to audit).
#   2. Add the entry with a reviewer signature and an expiry date (max 90 days).
#   3. Expired entries are treated as hard failures by CI; re-evaluate before extending.
#   4. The release-notes for the tag MUST link this file's diff so users see what is waived.
#
# Suppression entries are consumed by the govulncheck CI step (release workflow,
# job `govulncheck`). The step parses `govulncheck -json ./...`, extracts each
# `finding.osv` ID, subtracts the IDs listed here, and fails CI if any
# unsuppressed finding remains. Suppressed IDs are still printed as advisory
# output so reviewers see the active waiver list on every release.
#
# (No active suppressions as of v0.1.0.)
